{"id": 223727076, "title": "40 Killed In Katsina Bandit Attack", "text": "A dare-devil gang of bandits with dangerous weapons have attacked three village areas in Bakori local government area of Katsina, killing about forty people. Similarly, many houses were burnt down and properties worth millions of naira destroyed. The villages affected are Unguwar Lamido, Unguwar Kare and Unguwar Aro near Guga area. A report Daily Independent gathered stated that, the bandits attacked the villages between 1-2 am Saturday night. Already those killed had been buried according to Islamic injunctions, when contacted, the council chairman of Bakori local government council, Alhaji Ali Mamman Maicitta who attended the burial of the slained victims, said security agents were drafted to the scene of the incident. Maicitta also said the state government had been intimated of the incident, praying Allah to forgive those killed and their families, the fortitude to beat the loss.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"750\" height=\"499\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/Bandits-armed.webp\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/Bandits-armed.webp 750w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/Bandits-armed-300x200.webp 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></div>A dare-devil gang of bandits with dangerous weapons have attacked three village areas in Bakori local government area of Katsina, killing about forty people. Similarly, many houses were burnt down and properties worth millions of naira destroyed. The villages affected are Unguwar Lamido, Unguwar Kare and Unguwar Aro near Guga area. A report Daily Independent [&#8230;]", "url": "https://independent.ng/40-killed-in-katsina-bandit-attack/", "image": "https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/Bandits-armed.webp", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 14